Below is a set of TypeScript files for a distributed event broker. The broker has issues with message deduplication, connection timeout handling, and type narrowing in its event handlers.

1. Identify and explain every bug in detail, referencing the specific files and line numbers.
2. Provide the complete refactored implementation of all three files, ensuring all strict compiler checks pass, fixing all bugs, and adding comprehensive JSDoc comments.
3. Write a complete set of Jest unit tests (using ts-jest) to verify the fixes for deduplication and connection timeouts.

File 1: EventBroker.ts
```typescript
import { Event, EventHandler } from './EventTypes';
export class EventBroker {
  private handlers = new Map<string, EventHandler[]>();
  private processedEvents = new Set<string>();
  subscribe(topic: string, handler: EventHandler): void {
    if (!this.handlers.has(topic)) {
      this.handlers.set(topic, []);
    }
    this.handlers.get(topic)!.push(handler);
  }
  async publish(event: Event): Promise<void> {
    if (this.processedEvents.has(event.id)) return;
    this.processedEvents.add(event.id);
    const topicHandlers = this.handlers.get(event.topic);
    if (topicHandlers) {
      const promises = topicHandlers.map(h => h(event));
      await Promise.all(promises);
    }
  }
}
```

File 2: ConnectionManager.ts
```typescript
import { EventEmitter } from 'events';
export class ConnectionManager extends EventEmitter {
  private connections = new Map<string, any>();
  connect(connectionId: string, client: any): void {
    this.connections.set(connectionId, client);
    setTimeout(() => {
      if (this.connections.has(connectionId)) {
        this.emit('timeout', connectionId);
      }
    }, 5000);
  }
  disconnect(connectionId: string): void {
    this.connections.delete(connectionId);
  }
}
```

File 3: EventTypes.ts
```typescript
export interface Event {
  id: string;
  topic: string;
  payload: any;
}
export type EventHandler = (event: Event) => Promise<void> | void;
